## Layer 3: Resolution & Scoring (The Brain)

### ConfigResolver ([config_resolver.py](file:///d:/stockviedeo/stock-analyzer-app/config/config_resolver.py))

The **brain** of the application. 4188 lines, 74 methods. Two public APIs:

1. **[build_evaluation_context_only()](file:///d:/stockviedeo/stock-analyzer-app/config/config_resolver.py#635-676)** — Phase 1: Pure analysis (no capital/time dependency)
2. **[build_execution_context_from_evaluation()](file:///d:/stockviedeo/stock-analyzer-app/config/config_resolver.py#677-706)** — Phase 2: Execution projection

#### Evaluation Pipeline (8 Internal Phases)

```mermaid
graph TD
    P1["Phase 1: Flatten Indicators<br>_flatten_indicator_data()"]
    P2["Phase 2: Trend & Momentum<br>_build_trend_context()<br>_build_momentum_context()"]
    P3["Phase 3: Score Calculation<br>_calculate_all_scores()<br>tech + fundamental + hybrid"]
    P4["Phase 4: Setup Classification<br>_classify_setup()<br>Evaluate all 18 setups, rank by priority × fit"]
    P5["Phase 5: Strategy Classification<br>_classify_strategy()<br>Score all strategies via fit indicators"]
    P6["Phase 6: Confidence Calculation<br>_calculate_confidence()<br>Base floor → ADX bands → modifiers → clamp"]
    P7["Phase 7: Gate Validation<br>_validate_structural_gates()<br>_validate_execution_rules()<br>_validate_opportunity_gates()"]
    P8["Phase 8: Risk Candidates<br>_build_risk_candidates()<br>SL, targets, RR ratio"]
    
    P1 --> P2 --> P3 --> P4 --> P5 --> P6 --> P7 --> P8
```

#### Execution Pipeline (Built on top of evaluation)

```
_build_execution_context():
    ├── _build_entry_permission()     # Aggregate all evaluation validations
    ├── _build_position_sizing()      # Capital allocation
    ├── _finalize_risk_model()        # Quantity, risk amount, targets
    ├── _build_order_model()          # Market/limit/stop order type
    ├── _build_market_constraints()   # Indian market gates
    ├── _build_time_constraints()     # Avoidance windows
    └── _can_execute()                # Final go/no-go
```

### Multibagger Module (Liquid Hybrid Pipeline)

The Multibagger module operates as a parallel, specialized pipeline for high-conviction, long-term plays.

#### Phase 1: Bulk Screener ([multibagger_screener.py](file:///d:/stockviedeo/stock-analyzer-app/config/multibagger/multibagger_screener.py))
- **Multithreaded Bulk Scan**: Processes the entire `NSE_500` or custom universe in parallel (default 10 worker threads).
- **Hard Gatekeeper**: Filters based on Listing Age (min 5 years), Price Caps, Sector Exclusions, and "Distance from High" (max 25% from 52-week high).
- **Efficiency**: Only symbols passing Phase 1 proceed to the resource-heavy Phase 2.

#### Phase 2: Detailed Evaluator ([multibagger_evaluator.py](file:///d:/stockviedeo/stock-analyzer-app/config/multibagger/multibagger_evaluator.py))
- **Isolated Brain**: Uses a custom `MBQueryOptimizedExtractor` that bypasses the main pipeline's global state to avoid circular dependencies.
- **Deep Scoring**: Evaluates 4 Pillars (Growth, Profitability, Solvency, Technicals) using specialized MB scoring logic.
- **Persistence**: Results are upserted into the `MultibaggerCandidate` table (SQLite).

### Signal Engine ([signal_engine.py](file:///d:/stockviedeo/stock-analyzer-app/services/signal_engine.py))

Orchestrator that **triggers** the resolver:

| Function | Role |
|----------|------|
| [compute_all_profiles()](file:///d:/stockviedeo/stock-analyzer-app/services/signal_engine.py#366-629) | Loops over horizons, computes eligibility + opportunity scores |
| [calculate_structural_eligibility()](file:///d:/stockviedeo/stock-analyzer-app/services/signal_engine.py#72-134) | Blends tech/fund/hybrid pillars with horizon-specific weights |
| [compute_opportunity_score()](file:///d:/stockviedeo/stock-analyzer-app/services/signal_engine.py#136-311) | Layers patterns, setups, and strategy fit on eligibility |
| [generate_trade_plan()](file:///d:/stockviedeo/stock-analyzer-app/services/signal_engine.py#770-1114) | Builds eval_ctx → exec_ctx → enhancer → finalize |
| [finalize_trade_decision()](file:///d:/stockviedeo/stock-analyzer-app/services/signal_engine.py#633-748) | Maps gate outcomes to trade signals (BUY/HOLD/SELL) |

