## Signal Semantics

All signal states are **first-class outputs** with explicit, non-overlapping semantics. The system enforces a strict **"Neutral-to-WATCH"** standard.

| Signal | Condition | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| `STRONG_BUY` / `BUY` | All gates pass, confidence ≥ threshold, RR valid | Entry is structurally sound and timing is right. Execute. |
| `SELL` | Bearish direction, all gates pass | Short/exit entry. Direction-aware mirror of BUY. |
| `WATCH` | Neutral trend OR missing primary pattern | **DEFAULT FALLBACK.** Stock quality is good, but pattern/setup alignment is absent. (Layer 0 Block). |
| `HOLD` | Active position management only | Strictly for existing, open trades. **Never generated as a new entry evaluation.** |
| `BLOCKED` | Setup + pattern present but execution gate failed | Entry structure exists but a hard execution gate (spread cost, low RR floor, extreme volatility) prevents entry. |
| `AVOID` | Fundamental or macro red flags | Fundamental score too low or macro conditions completely adverse. |

**Architectural Invariant:** `WATCH` vs `BLOCKED`  
* `WATCH` = Stock is good, but waiting for a setup to physically form on the chart.  
* `BLOCKED` = Setup has formed, but it is mathematically unsafe to trade right now.

